main event: An oblong, bright orange object was observed in Palm Beach, Florida on December 6, 1954, for approximately 6-8 seconds.
interesting points: The object was very bright and orange-colored,The observation type included both ground-radar and air-visual,The object exhibited rapid changes in direction and altitude,Another observation described it as a bright cloud-like object with a round outline,The sighting concluded that there was insufficient information for evaluation.
